#: ../source/includes/apiargs/method-sh.shardCollection-options-param.rst:17
#: ../source/includes/apiargs/method-sh.shardCollection-options-param.rst:49
msgid ""
"Optional. Specifies the number of chunks to create initially when "
"sharding an *empty* collection with a :ref:`hashed shard key <sharding-"
"hashed-sharding>`. MongoDB will then create and balance chunks across the"
" cluster. The ``numInitialChunks`` must be less than ``8192`` per shard."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/includes/apiargs/method-sh.shardCollection-options-param.rst:25
#: ../source/includes/apiargs/method-sh.shardCollection-options-param.rst:57
msgid ""
"If the collection is not empty or the shard key is not a hashed key, the "
"operation returns an error."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/includes/apiargs/method-sh.shardCollection-options-param.rst:30
msgid "``collation``"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/includes/apiargs/method-sh.shardCollection-options-param.rst:34
#: ../source/includes/apiargs/method-sh.shardCollection-options-param.rst:64
msgid ""
"Optional. If the collection specified to ``shardCollection`` has a "
"default :doc:`collation </reference/collation>`, you *must* include a "
"collation document with ``{ locale : \"simple\" }``, or the "
"``shardCollection`` command fails. At least one of the indexes whose "
"fields support the shard key pattern must have the simple collation."
msgstr ""

